From ae66f0ad9dbe4331811607382851687d3c2497fd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 07:33:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Apply Apple-style ActionPilot AI redesign from Claude Design

Implements the design exported from Claude Design (indigo-accent, neutral
Apple-like palette, translucent sidebar, dark mode toggle) across the whole
app while preserving all existing Firebase/Gemini/Calendar functionality.

- Theme system: CSS custom properties for light/dark + 4 selectable accent
  colors, persisted zustand store, Tailwind tokens wired to the variables
- Reskinned all UI primitives (Button, Card, Badge, Input, Avatar, Modal)
  and layout (Sidebar with real nav icons + dark toggle, Topbar)
- Login/Onboarding: matches the prototype's card treatment; onboarding is
  now a real 2-step flow (workspace name -> working hours) that persists
  org.settings.workDayStart/End on finish
- Meeting detail: switched from tabs to the design's 2-column layout
  (summary+transcript / extracted tasks) with the floating Ask AI bar
- New meeting: circular record button + waveform as the primary capture
  affordance, with upload/dictation/upload-audio as source chips
  (extracted MediaRecorder logic into useAudioRecorder hook)
- Tasks: added client-side filter pills (All/To do/In progress/Completed)
- Scheduler, Dashboard, Search, Settings restyled to match; Settings gained
  a real Integrations section (Google Calendar connection status) and a
  working Notifications section backed by a new User.notifPrefs field
- Removed now-unused TaskInlineRow after the meeting-detail redesign

Omitted the design's "weekly trend" dashboard chart since there's no
backing historical data source (analytics is all-time only) - didn't want
to fabricate data for it.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
